{"title":"First Rides: Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch Enduro eBike, Smashing Downhill & Zipping Back Up!","link":"https://bikerumor.com/first-rides-marin-alpine-trail-e-bosch-enduro-ebike-smashing-downhill-zipping-back-up/","date":1717174475000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_NDS-riding-1536x1024.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"(Photo BCA/Mirror Media)\" /></p>\n<p>Last week Marin launched an all-new aluminum Alpine Trail E enduro ebike powered by the torquey Bosch CX with a big 750Wh battery. And it’s a beast. With all the big mountain travel and much of the adjustability of their recent “meat-powered” enduro bike, this pedal-assist enduro eMTB is a super capable ride. Ideal for mountain e-bikers looking to tackle the most technical trails, but with a powerful boost to get back up the hill fast for lap after lap good times…</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>2024 Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch 160mm alloy enduro ebike</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_ebike.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_ebike.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch eMTB, 160mm adjustable aluminum alloy enduro ebike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_ebike.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_ebike-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_ebike-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_ebike-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_ebike-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_ebike-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo Mountain Bike Connection Winter/Rupert Fowler)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Marin calls this new  Alpine Trail E Bosch ebike the “biggest, baddest beast” of their MTB lineup. A big step up from the previous eMTB generation of the Alpine Trail family, this new aluminum enduro ebike features: 10mm more travel front &amp; rear, an improved long-travel suspension design, more capable geometry, more rider style adjustability, a more powerful motor, and longer pedal-assist range. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>What’s new?</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_Bosch-CX-motor.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_Bosch-CX-motor.jpg\" alt=\"Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch 160mm alloy enduro ebike, Bosch CX motor\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_Bosch-CX-motor.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_Bosch-CX-motor-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_Bosch-CX-motor-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_Bosch-CX-motor-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_Bosch-CX-motor-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_Bosch-CX-motor-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_Bosch-CX-motor-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo BCA/Rupert Fowler)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The logical starting point is the switch to a Bosch ebike powertrain. Marin now powers the revamped Alpine Trail E with the popular 85Nm Bosch Performance CX motor. Inside its massive hydroformed downtube is a big 750Wh PowerTube battery, offering almost 50% more juice than the previous generation. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_Bosch-ebike-details.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_Bosch-ebike-details.jpg\" alt=\"Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch 160mm alloy enduro ebike, eMTB controls\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_Bosch-ebike-details.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_Bosch-ebike-details-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_Bosch-ebike-details-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_Bosch-ebike-details-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_Bosch-ebike-details-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_Bosch-ebike-details-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo BCA/Rupert Fowler)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>And it all is controlled by a tidy Bluetooth wireless lefthand thumb switch with a simple multi-color LED battery &amp; mode indicator just behind your headset.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>4-bar upgrade</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_4-bar-in-the-rain.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_4-bar-in-the-rain.jpg\" alt=\"Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch 160mm alloy enduro ebike, new 4-bar suspension\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_4-bar-in-the-rain.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_4-bar-in-the-rain-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_4-bar-in-the-rain-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_4-bar-in-the-rain-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_4-bar-in-the-rain-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_4-bar-in-the-rain-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_4-bar-in-the-rain-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo BCA/Rupert Fowler)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Next up, a new suspension design. The new Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch now gets 160mm of rear wheel travel paired to 170mm forks. That’s just 10mm more than the previous Shimano-powered eMTBs. But now it’s with a proper 4-bar suspension layout that promises more active suspension and a sense of even more travel (vs. the previous faux-bar design). Marin moves the rear end pivot onto the chainstay, calling it MultiTrac 2 LT. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s the same as on the newly updated regular <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/marin-alpine-trail-reshapes-all-new-super-adjustable-160mm-alloy-enduro-bike-1st-ride/\">Alpine Trail enduro bike</a>, and was created to “<em>reduce anti-rise, allowing for better chassis control while braking, more mid-stroke support, and better feel at bottom out</em>”. Marin describes it as a gamechanger for their longer travel bikes. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Adjustable enduro ebike geometry too!</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_climbing.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_climbing.jpg\" alt=\"Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch 160mm alloy enduro ebike, climbing\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_climbing.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_climbing-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_climbing-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_climbing-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_climbing-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_climbing-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_climbing-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo Mountain Bike Connection Winter/Mirror Media)\n</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Like the enduro bike, Marin makes their enduro ebike adjustable, as well.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_chainstay-flip-chip.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_chainstay-flip-chip.jpg\" alt=\"Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch 160mm alloy enduro ebike, geometry flip-chip\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_chainstay-flip-chip.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_chainstay-flip-chip-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_chainstay-flip-chip-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_chainstay-flip-chip-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_chainstay-flip-chip-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_chainstay-flip-chip-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Rupert-Fowler_chainstay-flip-chip-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo BCA/Rupert Fowler)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new MultiTrac 2 LT layout had the added benefit of neatly integrating a chainstay flip-chip to let riders easily swap chainstay length &amp; bottom bracket height depending on their preferred riding style. Pick a High bottom bracket/Short chainstay length for more agility or a Low/Long position for more stability. BB height and chainstay length both change by 7mm – a relatively small tweak to adapt the ebike to your preference, without doing anything too drastic.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-ebike_eccentric-adjustable-headset.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1125\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-ebike_eccentric-adjustable-headset.jpg\" alt=\"Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch 160mm alloy enduro ebike, adjustable headset\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-ebike_eccentric-adjustable-headset.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-ebike_eccentric-adjustable-headset-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-ebike_eccentric-adjustable-headset-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-ebike_eccentric-adjustable-headset-120x68.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-ebike_eccentric-adjustable-headset-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-ebike_eccentric-adjustable-headset-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It also gets an adjustable headset. That means the new ebike starts with a Zero-offset headset. Or you can drop in the angle-adjust upper headset cup and change the head angle by +/-0.6°. Don’t worry, no internal cables through the headset, so this is a quick and easy change.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_geometry-options-scaled.jpg\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_geometry-options-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch eMTB, 160mm adjustable aluminum alloy enduro ebike, geometry\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_geometry-options-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_geometry-options-297x149.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_geometry-options-1536x768.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_geometry-options-120x60.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_geometry-options-768x384.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_geometry-options-2048x1024.jpg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>(<em>click to zoom</em>)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>From its low position baseline, the new Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch aims to be a bit more modern geometry-wise compared to its same-travel predecessor. But the old bike was already quite long &amp; slack, so no huge changes. Now with just 3 sizes available – M-XL (but no more S) – these sizes gets wider Reach range, generally shifting rider weight forward, while still fitting most riders. Seattube are a bit steeper to match, as well.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Its headtube angle starts the same in Low mode at 63°, or half a degree steeper from the High mode starting point at 63.5°, hinting at a bit more agility. But with the adjustable upper cup, head angles go as slack as 62.4° or as steep as 64°.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Tech details</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_angled-detail.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_angled-detail.jpg\" alt=\"Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch 160mm alloy enduro ebike, eMTB frame detail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_angled-detail.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_angled-detail-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_angled-detail-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_angled-detail-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_angled-detail-768x576.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new aluminum Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch now features a new 34.9mm dropper post diameter, UDH for future-proof drivetrains, and conventional internal cable routing through ports in the sides of the downtube with rubber membrane seals to keep the elements out.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Marin gives the Alpine Trail E lots of heavy-duty frame protection. There’s wrap-around rubber chainstay guard and seatstay protectors to ward off chain rattle. And also the big 30% fiberglass-infused-nylon downtube and motor casing protection.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Riding Impressions</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_wet-rocky-trails.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_wet-rocky-trails.jpg\" alt=\"Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch 160mm alloy enduro ebike, rocky &amp; wet riding\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_wet-rocky-trails.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_wet-rocky-trails-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_wet-rocky-trails-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_wet-rocky-trails-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_wet-rocky-trails-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_wet-rocky-trails-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_wet-rocky-trails-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo BCA/Mirror Media)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I ride a lot of steep rocky trails, so I really like the ability to set the ebike up with the Higher bottom bracket / Shorter chainstay position, while still being able to pick how steep I want the head angle. Frankly, I feel like 63.5° in my preferred 0-offset is plenty slack, while still being able to muscle this heavy ebike around tight turns. But, it’s nice to know that I could make it slacker if ended up riding more on faster, straighter trails.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_steep-climb.jpg\"><img width=\"1800\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_steep-climb.jpg\" alt=\"Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch 160mm alloy enduro ebike, steep climbs\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_steep-climb.jpg 1800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_steep-climb-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_steep-climb-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_steep-climb-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_steep-climb-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_steep-climb-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_steep-climb-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo BCA/Mirror Media)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>I had not ridden the previous Alpine Trail E, so can’t attest to its relative improvements. But I did get to smash this version down a mix of steep rocky trails, tight &amp; slick technical tracks, and high-speed open singletrack. And the new Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch just smashes down the hills, and was happy to help spin me back up to the top to do it again and again. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_jumping.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_jumping.jpg\" alt=\"Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch 160mm alloy enduro ebike, aitime\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_jumping.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_jumping-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_jumping-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_jumping-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_jumping-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_jumping-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-160mm-alloy-enduro-eMTB_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_jumping-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo BCA/Mirror Media)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, it’s undeniable that this is a heavy ebike. Beefy alloy frame + big Bosch motor &amp; mega battery + e-enduro capable components… all adds up. The large E2 that I tested weighed 27.8kg (61.3lb) without pedals. It takes quite a bit of muscle to push that around on tight trails. But the geometry seemed well-matched to the weight. And the Alpine Trail E liked to stay planted on the trail. A side benefit to smaller, lighter riders though, is you’ll have no trouble getting an active suspension feel.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One tiny, but super-appreciated detail. Sure, it’s nice that the ebike comes spec’d with sticky <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/vee-tire-gravity-mtb-adds-new-snap-wce-mk2-wlt-simplifies-enduro-dh-emtb-casings/\" target=\"_blank\">Vee tires</a> that I know. But also that Marin actually spec’s these ebikes with <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/review-cushcore-pro-inserts-allow-crazy-low-tire-pressures-for-ultimate-grip/\" target=\"_blank\">Cush Core Pro</a> tire inserts and their own sealant, straight off the bikeshop floor.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>2024 Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch – Pricing, options &amp; availability</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Marin only has two models of the new Alpine Trail E Bosch ebike. Both share the same 160mm travel Series 4 Aluminum frame, Bosch Performance CX motor, and 750Wh internal battery. And they both also get a mixed 29/27.5″ mullet wheel size setup. Plus, 170mm forks, powerful 4-piston brakes, and big 203mm rotors to bring these beasts to a stop.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_AT-E1.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_AT-E1.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Marin Alpine Trail E1 Bosch enduro ebike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_AT-E1.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_AT-E1-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_AT-E1-1536x922.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_AT-E1-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_AT-E1-768x461.jpg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>2024 Marin Alpine Trail E1 Bosch</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Alpine Trail E1 Bosch is more of the entry point at $5700 /6300€ with a Marzocchi Z1 fork &amp; CR Coil shock, a Shimano <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/shimano-cues-mid-tier-mtb-groups-intercompatible-9-10-11-speed-components-affordable-1x/\" target=\"_blank\">CUES</a> 10-speed LinkGlide drivetrain, and TRP Slate EVO brakes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_AT-E2.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_AT-E2.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Marin Alpine Trail E2 Bosch enduro ebike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_AT-E2.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_AT-E2-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_AT-E2-1536x922.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_AT-E2-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_AT-E2-768x461.jpg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>2024 Marin Alpine Trail E2 Bosch</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The ebike I tested was the $6600 / 7250€ Marin Alpine Trail E2 Bosch with a Fox 38 Performance Elite fork, DHX2 Performance Elite coil shock, an XT 12-speed drivetrain, and powerful TRP DH-R EVO brakes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_climbing.jpg\"><img width=\"2000\" height=\"1200\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_climbing.jpg\" alt=\"2024 Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch eMTB, 160mm adjustable aluminum alloy enduro ebike, climbing\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_climbing.jpg 2000w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_climbing-297x178.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_climbing-1536x922.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_climbing-120x72.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-Marin-Alpine-Trail-E-Bosch-eMTB_160mm-adjustable-aluminum-alloy-enduro-ebike_BCA-photo-by-Mirror-Media_climbing-768x461.jpg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo BCA/Mirror Media)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Both are available now through your local Marin dealer bikeshop. The old Shimano versions of the Alpine Trail E carry over without the newfound adjustability, but now with lower pricing.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.marinbikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">MarinBikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/first-rides-marin-alpine-trail-e-bosch-enduro-ebike-smashing-downhill-zipping-back-up/\">First Rides: Marin Alpine Trail E Bosch Enduro eBike, Smashing Downhill &amp; Zipping Back Up!</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Cory Benson","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"fd99421d59d417326759a8cf190fff96fe1bb84a3e780fad9645fe6f25176453","category":"Cycling"}